    {
        "content": "<p>The syntax <code> `($x)</code> is for syntax quotations, which is different from the <code> `String</code> from before, which is a name literal.</p>\n<p>(In general, \"this does not work\" is not a question. What error do you see? What question do you have about the error?)</p>\n<p>One hint is that you can look at the source for a command like <code>#print</code> or <code>#check</code> for inspiration.</p>",
        "id": 449544153,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1720292168
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I want to implement a <code>#doc</code> command such that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>#doc x</code> shows the content of docstring of <code>x</code></li>\n<li>if <code>x</code> has no docstring, <code>#doc x</code> should return empty string. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>following code is my attempt, but got an error.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"#doc\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">ident</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">command</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">run_meta</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">do</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">some</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">findDocString</span><span class=\"bp\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">getEnv</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failure</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">logInfo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">!</span><span class=\"s2\">\"{s}\"</span>\n<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">application type mismatch</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  @findDocString? __do_lift✝ do</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">    let info ← MonadRef.mkInfoFromRefPos</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">    let scp ← getCurrMacroScope</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">    let mainModule ← getMainModule</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">    pure</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">        {</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">          raw :=</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">            Syntax.ident info \"String\".toSubstring' (addMacroScope mainModule `String scp)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">              [Syntax.Preresolved.decl `String [], Syntax.Preresolved.namespace `String] }</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">argument</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  do</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">    let info ← MonadRef.mkInfoFromRefPos</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">    let scp ← getCurrMacroScope</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">    let mainModule ← getMainModule</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">    pure</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">        {</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">          raw :=</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">            Syntax.ident info \"String\".toSubstring' (addMacroScope mainModule `String scp)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">              [Syntax.Preresolved.decl `String [], Syntax.Preresolved.namespace `String] }</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">has type</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ?m.1089 (TSyntax `term) : Type</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">but is expected to have type</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  Name : Type</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">doc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">String</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 449596851,
        "sender_full_name": "Asei Inoue",
        "timestamp": 1720322100
    },
