        "timestamp": 1720335088
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I’m writing a Lean reference “Lean by Example” (<a href=\"https://lean-ja.github.io/lean-by-example/\">https://lean-ja.github.io/lean-by-example/</a>) and sometimes I want to display docstring in the book. </p>\n<p>But robust way is required because Lean is updated monthly.</p>",
        "id": 449613854,
        "sender_full_name": "Asei Inoue",
        "timestamp": 1720335217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>“copy paste doc string” is fragile, which doesn’t raise a warning/error when docstring is updated…</p>",
        "id": 449613966,
        "sender_full_name": "Asei Inoue",
        "timestamp": 1720335310
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not at a computer right now, but <code> `()</code> and <code>run_meta</code> are more or less inverses of each other in this context, so you should be able to remove both.  And instead of <code> `($x)</code> something like <code>x.getId</code> should work.  More robust would be to use <code>realizeGlobalConst</code> (or something similar) but you may need to initialize a <code>CoreM</code> lift for that.</p>",
        "id": 449630136,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1720346179
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Elab</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Command</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">DocString</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Elab</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Command</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">elab</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"#doc\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">ident</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">command</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">do</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">some</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">findDocString?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">getEnv</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">liftCoreM</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">do</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">realizeGlobalConstNoOverload</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">logInfo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m!</span><span class=\"s2\">\"{s}\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">`String` is the type of (UTF-8 encoded) strings.</span>\n\n<span class=\"cm\">The compiler overrides the data representation of this type to a byte sequence,</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">and both `String.utf8ByteSize` and `String.length` are cached and O(1).</span>\n\n<span class=\"cm\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">doc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">String</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 449639418,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1720350874
    }
]